'''Ardon Jashari''' (born 30 July 2002) is a Swiss professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{Italian football updater|Milan}} club [[AC Milan]] and the [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland national team]].

==Club career==
===Luzern===
Jashari made his professional debut with [[FC Luzern|Luzern]] in a 2–1 [[Swiss Super League]] victory against [[FC Zürich|Zürich]] on 31 July 2020.<ref name="Soccerway 2020">{{cite web | title=Luzern vs. Zürich|url=https://ca.soccerway.com/matches/2020/07/31/switzerland/super-league/fc-luzern/fc-zurich/3037986/|website=Soccerway | date=31 July 2020 | access-date=16 August 2020}}</ref>

===Club Brugge===
In April 2024, it was announced that Jashari would join [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] in the summer, having agreed a four-year contract.<ref name="wyrsch">{{cite news |last=Wyrsch |first=Daniel |title=Jetzt ist es fix: Ardon Jashari wechselt nach Belgien |trans-title=Now it's finalised: Ardon Jashari moves to Belgium |url=https://www.luzernerzeitung.ch/sport/fcluzern/fc-luzern-jetzt-ist-es-fix-ardon-jashari-wechselt-zum-fc-bruegge-fuer-6-millionen-euro-ld.2602434 |access-date=19 June 2024|newspaper=[[Luzerner Zeitung]] |date=3 April 2024 |language=de}}</ref> The transfer fee was reported as €6 million, a club record for FC Luzern.<ref name="wyrsch" />

Jashari had a strong first season in midfield for Club Brugge as they won the [[2024–25 Belgian Cup|Belgian Cup]],<ref>{{Cite web |title="Ik zei: kom, we zetten ons": Romeo Vermant doet verhaal achter hét beeld van bekerfinale en ziet "stoutste droom" uitkomen|trans-title="I said: come on, let's sit down": Romeo Vermant tells the story behind the image of the cup final and sees his "wildest dream" come true|url=https://sporza.be/nl/2025/05/04/-ik-zei-kom-we-zetten-ons-romeo-vermant-doet-verhaal-achter-het-beeld-van-bekerfinale-en-ziet-stoutste-droom-uitkomen~1746381223873/ |website=Sporza|date=4 May 2025 |access-date=28 May 2025|language=nl}}</ref> finished second in the Belgian Pro League behind [[Union Saint-Gilloise]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Het sprookje krijgt nu wél een happy end: Union kroont zich na 90 jaar opnieuw tot landskampioen na nerveuze titelzege|trans-title=The fairytale now has a happy ending: Union is crowned national champion again after 90 years after a nervous title victory|url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/jupiler-pro-league/2024-2025/champions-play-offs/10/union-kaa-gent-het-sprookje-krijgt-nu-wel-een-happy-end-union-kroont-zich-na-90-jaar-opnieuw-tot-landskampioen-na-nerveuze-titelzege~1720020842964/ |website=Sporza|date=25 May 2025 |access-date=28 May 2025|language=nl}}</ref> and qualified for the knockout stages of the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League]], losing to [[Aston Villa]] in the first knockout round.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Club Brugge overschouwt trots CL-campagne waarin het wedijverde met Europese top: "Ambitie om dat te blijven doen"|trans-title=Club Brugge proudly reflects on CL campaign in which it competed with the European top: "Ambition to continue doing so"|url=https://sporza.be/nl/2025/03/13/club-brugge-overschouwt-trots-cl-campagne-waarin-het-wedijverde-met-europese-top-ambitie-om-dat-te-blijven-doen~1741868431465/ |website=Sporza|date=13 March 2025 |access-date=28 May 2025|language=nl}}</ref>

Jashari was rewarded for his efforts by being voted both Player of the Year and Young Player of the Year at the [[Belgian professional football awards|Pro League Awards]].<ref name="JashariAward">{{Cite web |title=Ontdek hier alle winnaars van de Pro League Awards|trans-title=Discover all the winners of the Pro League Awards here |url=https://www.proleague.be/nieuws/ontdek-hier-alle-winnaars-van-de-pro-league-awards |website=Belgian Pro League|date=26 May 2025 |access-date=28 May 2025|language=nl}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Club-speler Ardon Jashari verkozen tot Speler van het Seizoen op Pro League Awards, Pocognoli Coach van het Seizoen|trans-title=Club player Ardon Jashari voted Player of the Season at Pro League Awards, Pocognoli Coach of the Season|url=https://sporza.be/nl/2025/05/26/club-speler-ardon-jashari-verkozen-tot-speler-van-het-seizoen-op-pro-league-awards-pocognoli-coach-van-het-seizoen~1748254654065/ |website=Sporza|date=26 May 2025 |access-date=28 May 2025|language=nl}}</ref>

===AC Milan===
On 6 August 2025, Jashari joined Italian [[Serie A]] club [[AC Milan]] on a five-year-deal.<ref>{{cite news |date=6 August 2025 |title=Official Statement: Ardon Jashari |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/media/2025-08-06/official-statement-ardon-jashari |access-date=6 August 2025 |publisher=[[AC Milan]]}}</ref>

==International career==
On 27 September 2022, Jashari debuted for the [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland national team]] in a [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League A|Nations League]] match against the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]], replacing [[Remo Freuler]] in extra-time.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Daniel|last=Wyrsch|title=Ardon Jashari: Schweizer WM-Fahrer mit 20 – ein toller Erfolg für die FCL-Nachwuchsförderung|url=https://www.luzernerzeitung.ch/sport/fcluzern/schweizer-katar-kader-ardon-jashari-schweizer-wm-fahrer-mit-20-ein-toller-erfolg-fuer-die-fcl-nachwuchsfoerderung-ld.2370704|newspaper=Luzerner Zeitung|date=9 November 2022|access-date=5 June 2025|language=de}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Born in [[Cham, Switzerland]], Jashari is of [[ethnic Albanian]] descent from [[Kumanovo]], [[North Macedonia]].<ref name="Fakti Ditor 2018">{{cite web | title=Ardon Jashari-talenti nga Kumanova që po pushton futbollin zviceran | website=Fakti Ditor | date=31 May 2018 | url=http://www.faktiditor.ch/ardon-jashari-talenti-nga-kumanova-qe-po-pushton-futbollin-zviceran/ | language=sq | access-date=16 August 2020}}</ref>

